%% Diagram: Cursor pagination — feed state lifecycle
%% Type: state
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle: cursor = null
    Idle --> Loading: sentinel intersects /<br/>fetchNextPage(cursor)
    Loading --> Loading: duplicate trigger ignored<br/>(in-flight token set)
    Loading --> AppendingPage: 2xx response,<br/>nextCursor present
    Loading --> EndOfStream: 2xx response,<br/>nextCursor = null
    Loading --> Error: 4xx 5xx network
    Error --> Retrying: backoff + jitter<br/>(only on retryable status)
    Retrying --> Loading: retry count <= max
    Retrying --> Failed: retry count exceeded
    Failed --> Loading: user taps Retry
    AppendingPage --> Idle: cursor := nextCursor,<br/>append items, evict if<br/>pages > maxPages
    EndOfStream --> [*]

    note right of AppendingPage
        Optimistic top-insert:
        new banner, no scroll jump.
        Anchor preserved with
        overflow-anchor: auto.
    end note
    note right of Error
        Retryable: 408, 429, 5xx, network.
        Non-retryable: 400, 401, 403, 404.
    end note
